# Blog Post Voice

Write in **agency voice**, not individual voice. Tiger Team Studios is a studio; the blog speaks for the team.

**Use "we" instead of "I":**
- "We built..." not "I built..."
- "We shipped..." not "I shipped..."
- "We wanted..." not "I wanted..."
- "We learned..." not "I learned..."
- "We're still figuring out..." not "I'm still figuring out..."

**Section headings:** Prefer "What We Were Playing With" over "What I Was Playing With". Same for "How We Prompted It", "What We Learned", etc.

**Descriptions and meta:** "How we wired up..." not "How I wired up...". "What we shipped..." not "What I shipped...".

Keep the same conversational, practical tone—just plural.
